[SN]TITLE[SN]
'Dangerous' mental health patient Reece Burton found

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A "dangerous" psychiatric patient who absconded from a London clinic has been found after a police manhunt.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Reece Burton, 25, was attending the North London Clinic in Edmonton, Enfield on permitted ground leave when he absconded on 20 November.
He had earlier been convicted of grievous bodily harm with intent and the Met Police issued warnings he was dangerous.
Burton was found in the Chelmsford area on Friday, Met Police said.
"Burton has now been returned to custody where he will no longer pose a threat to the public or himself," Det Supt Simon Warwick of the Met Police said.
